    "cross_module_architecture": {
      "evidence": [
        "README.md defines explicit governance and quality-gate scope for boundary-sensitive areas and explicitly names contract files for upload/startram checks, but the same level of explicit cross-module contract governance is not documented for wireguard protocol/config runtime boundaries.",
        "goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go uses namespace-based contract discovery (`SupportedActions`, `ActionMetas`) and an explicit parse boundary (`ParseAction`), indicating a stable transport-contract seam that should ideally be paired with a contract/compatibility policy artifact.",
        "goseg/config/wireguard.go introduces a runtime seam (`wireguardRuntime`) for filesystem and config-channel inputs, which is good for isolation but is not linked to an owning compatibility contract in the docs.",
        "goseg/startram/errors.go imports and relies on shared masking policy (`errpolicy.WrapMasked`) with a stable public message constant, showing a clear boundary contract between internal transport errors and outward API semantics."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": "Add a single consolidated governance section for protocol/config/stability contracts in README or dedicated docs that explicitly calls out wireguard action/config contract expectations and versioning compatibility behavior, matching the rigor already described for upload and startram edges."
    },
    "test_strategy": {
      "evidence": [
        "README.md’s Backend Quality Gate mandates contract-oriented checks for specific packages and mentions contract gate paths that include `goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go` and `goseg/startram/errors.go`.",
        "The same quality gate text uses explicit file targeting and does not state equivalent contract-test criteria for `goseg/config/wireguard.go` despite this file defining runtime-state mutation APIs (e.g., `CreateDefaultWGConf`, `updateWGConf`, `CycleWgKey`).",
        "In `goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go`, the exported discovery/parse helpers are core protocol boundary APIs (`ParseAction`, `SupportedActions`, `ActionMetas`) and therefore require deterministic, drift-sensitive tests as part of the same contract envelope."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": "Introduce an explicit cross-module contract test matrix for wireguard config mutations and action-contract compatibility (including malformed/invalid transitions), so test requirements are uniformly enforced rather than relying on implicit package-level coverage."
    }
  },
  "findings": [],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Documentation-driven contract policy is uneven across bounded modules: some transport/error surfaces have explicit gate requirements while other mutable-runtime surfaces do not.",
      "Quality coverage is not consistently framed as a policy for all governance-relevant boundaries, so contract drift risk is uneven by module."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [],
    "possible_false_positives": [
      "If the team intentionally treats wireguard/config as non-contract-governed internals, the cross-module documentation gap may be by design rather than a defect."
